## Overview

Analogous to #2993 `ReflectionUtils.findFields()` can return duplicate fields, breaking certain use cases.

In general, this can happen if an interface defines a field and a type hierarchy implements that same interface multiple times.

In JUnit Jupiter, this can result in a `static` `@TempDir` field from an interface being processed twice.

## Example

Given the following types, searching for `static` fields in `SubclassWithFieldAndFieldFromInterface` finds the `interfacePath` field twice.

```java
interface InterfaceWithField {

	String interfacePath = "ifc";
}
```

```java
class SuperclassWithFieldAndFieldFromInterface implements InterfaceWithField {

	static final String superPath = "super";
}
```

```java
class SubclassWithFieldAndFieldFromInterface extends SuperclassWithFieldAndFieldFromInterface
		implements InterfaceWithField {

	static final String subPath = "sub";
}
```

